# Use `br merge-driver` to merge `.beads/issues.jsonl` semantically.
#
# The default text merger sees parallel branches as conflicting whenever
# both touch the JSONL (e.g. branch A closes bead X, branch B closes
# bead Y). `br merge-driver` reads each side as a set of bead records
# and unions them semantically — only flagging conflicts when the SAME
# bead is modified incompatibly on both sides.
#
# Setup (per-clone — git won't honor a committed driver definition for
# security reasons):
#
#   git config --local merge.beads-jsonl.name "beads_rust JSONL semantic merge"
#   git config --local merge.beads-jsonl.driver "br merge-driver %O %A %B"
#
# jj users: add the matching merge-tool to ~/.config/jj/config.toml — see
# docs/beads-merge-driver-setup.md.
.beads/issues.jsonl merge=beads-jsonl
